# Introduction

Streaminer is a tool that provides a set of operators for mining data streams.
The interface is the R language, which automatically deploys the schematic to the
target stream processing system through a plugin.


# Python Bindings

Uses JPype for bringing Java to Python.

http://jpype.sourceforge.net/
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/14233802/are-there-any-distributed-machine-learning-libraries-for-using-python-with-hadoo
https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/MAHOUT/Using+Mahout+with+Python+via+JPype


# R Bindings

http://www.rforge.net/rJava/
http://darrenjw.wordpress.com/2011/01/01/calling-java-code-from-r/


Based on:

- stream-lib: cardinality, set membership, top-k elements and frequency
  https://github.com/addthis/stream-lib
  
- stream-mining: quantiles, top-k, bayes, ...
  https://bitbucket.org/cbockermann/stream-mining
  
- MOA (Massive Online Analysis): machine learning algorithms (classification, regression, clustering, outlier detection and recommender systems) and tools for evaluation.
  http://moa.cms.waikato.ac.nz/
  
- SAMOA
  https://github.com/yahoo/samoa
